The paper is about computer vision (CV) and specifically focuses on the combination of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and conditional random fields (CRFs) for semantic image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses optimization algorithms and back-propagation, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of CRFs for modeling flexible higher order interactions is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions parallelism, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
